In a bowl, combine bread crumbs and butter. Set aside. In a separate bowl, combine pears, cranberries, stevia and lemon juice. Spread one-third of the bread crumb mixture in prepared stoneware. Layer half the pear mixture over top. Repeat. Finish with a layer of crumbs and pour cranberry juice over top. Cover and cook on High for 4 hours, until fruit is tender and mixture is hot and bubbly.